<title>GERMANY: Opel says 1996 profit falls to 314 mln dmk.</title>
<headline>Opel says 1996 profit falls to 314 mln dmk.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1997-06-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Calendar 1996</p>
<p>(in millions of marks unless stated)</p>
<p>    Group net profit			   314     vs 363</p>
<p>    Group pre-tax profit		     477     vs 401</p>
<p>    Group sales				  28,300  vs 25,900</p>
<p>    Group return on sales		    1.7 pct vs 1.5 pct</p>
<p>NOTE - Full name of the German carmaker is Adam Opel AG, a unit of U.S. carmaker General Motors Corp.</p>
<p>Opel said the sales level was the second-highest level in its history but that the lower net profit was due to higher tax payments.</p>
<p>Opel said the higher 1996 sales were due mostly to an improvement in its model offerings and also through higher sales of the Opel Vectra and 50,0000 units of the Cadillac Catera, a version of its Opel Omega sold in the United States.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
